The paper deals with machine learning techniques, specifically deep neural networks, and their vulnerability to adversarial attacks in the context of autonomous driving. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for autonomous driving, and robotics (cs.RO) for simulating the attacks. Finally, the paper also discusses the security implications of the attacks, which suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
